"SYNOPSIS: Apcupsd power protection for your LFS connected to an APC UPS via "
"serial port.    \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apcupsd-serial.txt:23
msgid ""
"DESCRIPTION: This hint describes the installation of Apcupsd software on an "
"LFS based computer protected by an American Power Conversion (APC) "
"uinterruptible power supply connected via serial cable.  The normal software "
"installation analyzes the sytem to determine a standard linux distribution "
"so that scripts may be installed to their proper place. Because LFS is "
"nonstandard the installation is not completed and left to the user.  This "
"hint describes the steps needed to complete the software installation on an "
"LFS system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apcupsd-serial.txt:28
msgid ""
"PREREQUISITES: This hint will work on any LFS system although the "
"bootscripts may need minor modifications.  This is especially true of older "
"LFS systems where the bootscripts were NOT in the /etc/rc.d/init.d "
"directory."
msgstr ""

