msgid ""
"1. Introduction\n"
"=================\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apcupsd-serial.txt:60
msgid ""
"Apcupsd is useful for controlling American Power Conversion's (APC)  "
"uninterruptiple power supplies (UPS).  Apcupsd monitors the UPS and during a "
"power loss, informs the system users of the failure, and if power is not "
"restored, safely shuts down the system.  The Apcupsd manual (available on "
"line at http://www.sibbald.com/apcupsd/manual/index.html or with the "
"software)  provides excellent instructions on installing and configuring the "
"software.  The configure script can identify several standard linux "
"distributions and make the correct installation. However, as LFS is by "
"design not standard this hint provides the information to protect an LFS "
"system with an APC UPS connected via a serial connection using Apcupsd "
"software."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apcupsd-serial.txt:63
msgid ""
"If you are using an APC UPS that connects via USB please see the hint by "
"Bryan Mason."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apcupsd-serial.txt:66
msgid ""
"The installation of Apcupsd is mostly straightforward until \"make install\" "
"is completed. Then the LFS user will see the following series of messages:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apcupsd-serial.txt:72
msgid ""
"\"Unknown distribution You have to manually install apcupsd boot script and "
"halt script for clean emergency shutdown.  Please contribute your "
"distribution install to apcupsd team.  I'm sorry: you are on your own.\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apcupsd-serial.txt:75
msgid ""
"The purpose of this hint is to provide one method of accomplishing the above "
"actions to get Apcupsd up and running on the LFS \"unknown\" distribution."
msgstr ""

